  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Perennial or winter annual herb from Plantaginaceae, native to temperate Eurasia, now cosmopolitan. Not the cooking banana (Musa). Basal rosette of broad, ovate leaves with prominent parallel veining. Produces dense, slender inflorescences (spikes) of inconspicuous flowers. Ubiquitous medicinal \"weed\" with multi-civilizational use: Ayurveda, Traditional Chinese Medicine, Traditional Persian Medicine, Ojibwe/Iroquois/Menominee herbalism, European folk medicine. Leaf poultice is most universal medicinal application—emollient, vulnerary, antimicrobial. Contains tannins, iridoid glycosides, mucilage.",
